=== Architect entry (2026-07-06) — Fix Cycle 2 ===

Deliverable: docs/adr-phase-2-tools-safety.md §12 (Fix Cycle 2 section)

Bug found (post-merge, pre-tester): checkPrefix resolves root via filepath.Abs
only, but every abspath it receives has been through filepath.EvalSymlinks (via
resolveScoped or resolvePartial). If the project root sits behind a symlink in
its own ancestry, the two sides of the prefix comparison are on different
resolution bases — legitimate paths spuriously fail with PathEscapeError.

This was not caught by Phase 2's tester because the existing symlink test
(TestResolveScoped_SymlinkEscape) covers a symlink inside the project pointing
outside it (child-path case), not a symlink in the root's own ancestry.

Fix applied to ADR (no code changed yet — Architect specifies, Builder
implements):

1. checkPrefix: replace filepath.Abs(root) with filepath.EvalSymlinks(root)
   first, then filepath.Abs(evalRoot). If EvalSymlinks fails (root doesn't
   exist), fall back to the original root value (one Abs call still follows).

2. NewDefaultRegistry: optionally resolve projectRoot via EvalSymlinks at
   construction time. Not strictly required for the checkPrefix fix, but
   needed for AllowPath correctness when both glob restrictions and a
   symlinked root exist. Documented as a recommendation for the builder
   implementing this cycle.

3. AllowPath (tools.go): identified as having the same root-vs-path
   mismatched resolution issue (via filepath.Rel against c.ProjectRoot).
   But since ToolConfig is constructed by Phase 3's turn loop (not yet
   built), the fix is to ensure ToolConfig.ProjectRoot is the symlink-
   resolved root. Phase 3's builder should read it from any tool struct's
   resolved root field. Documented in ADR §12.5.

No changes needed to resolveScoped, resolvePartial, or error types.
No existing test behavior changes — all cases verified in §12.6 of the ADR.
The fix adds one EvalSymlinks call on root per file-tool invocation (same
cost as the existing child-path EvalSymlinks, typically cheaper since root
is shorter).

Flag to builder implementing the code change:
- The fix goes in internal/tools/resolve.go, function checkPrefix, lines 47-51.
- Optionally also fix NewDefaultRegistry to resolve root once at startup
  (internal/tools/tools.go, function NewDefaultRegistry, line 54-63).
- Add a unit test for the symlinked-root scenario (simulate via a temp dir
  with a symlink "root" pointing to another temp dir, then verify resolveScoped
  against the symlink root succeeds).
